          "body": "Once Jesus has named the *paidion* as the kingdom’s standard, He turns to those who would harm such ones. Verses 6-9 contain some of His strongest threats anywhere: the millstone-drowning is *preferable* to causing a little one to stumble; self-amputation is *better than* Gehenna. Verse 10 forbids *despising* (*kataphroneo*) the little ones, on the ground that their angels continually behold the Father’s face — a remarkable disclosure of heavenly intercession-presence for the marginal. Verses 12-14 then ground the protection in the Father’s own pursuit: the shepherd leaves the ninety-nine for the one, and *it is not the will of your Father that one of these little ones perish* (v.14). The section moves from negative warning (don’t scandalize, don’t despise) to positive pursuit (seek the wandering)."
