          "title": "The chapter’s pastoral integration",
          "body": "The four movements form one argument. Greatness through humility (1-5) makes possible the protection of the little ones (6-14) which is enacted institutionally as restorative discipline (15-20) and personally as unbounded forgiveness (21-35). Each movement is grounded in *the Father in heaven* (vv.10, 14, 19, 35) and each is bracketed by *the kingdom of heaven* (vv.1, 23). The chapter’s deepest pastoral move is theological: the church’s ethics toward one another are not freestanding rules but the visible reproduction of how God in Christ has dealt with us. The forgiven forgive, the welcomed welcome, the pursued pursue. To refuse is to reveal that you have not yet truly received."
